songs.title: Paper Chasin’*
songs.lyrics:
Lyrics from snippet

[Verse]
Paper chasin' on occasion, West Deer Park, that's my location
Life and death what we was facin', boy gotta get that motivation
Back in the basement, look at my idols, I'm feelin' adjacent
Doin' the shit that I wish I was doing, I'm feelin' impatient
Throwin' parties and catchin' cases, that's the life, but that shit is basic
I've cooked crack and I can't erase it
Brothers on the corner sellin' rock, throwin' parties, and catchin' cases
Grew up all alone, had to teach myself just how to tie my laces
What's the deal? I'ma play the field
RattPack know we keep it real
[?] love to the people that
[?] brother like me
[?] can't forget those
[?] today

Even if I could, I would not
